title: Despite losing perfect record, North Korea stays atop World Cup qualifying group with 0-0 draw
text:
Despite losing perfect record, North Korea stays atop World Cup qualifying group with 0-0 draw By JOHN DUERDEN Associated Press   6:05   6:05   
Subjects: 
SEOUL, South Korea — North Korea's perfect record in World Cup qualifying came to an end Thursday after being held to a 0-0 draw by the Philippines. 
The North Koreans lead Group H with 10 points from four games. 
Also, an injury-time goal from Abu Nahyeh gave Palestine a 1-1 draw against East Timor. 
The top team from each of the eight groups and the best four second-place teams advance to the final round of qualifying.
